@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    Your privacy is important to us.
    This privacy policy explains how the Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS) collects, uses, and protects your personal information.
    The CMCS is designed to streamline the submission and approval of monthly claims for Independent Contractor (IC) lecturers,
    involving interactions between lecturers, HR personnel, and Academic Managers.
</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect and process various types of personal data to facilitate the monthly claims submission and approval process:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> This includes your name, email address, phone number, and role within the system (e.g., Lecturer, HR, Academic Manager).</li>
    <li><strong>Employment Details:</strong> Data related to your work, including hours worked, hourly rate, and claim amounts.</li>
    <li><strong>Supporting Documents:</strong> Any documents you upload to support your claim, such as time sheets, contracts, or invoices.</li>
    <li><strong>System Interactions:</strong> We track interactions with the system, including the dates and times of claim submissions and approvals.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>Your personal data is used for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To facilitate the submission and processing of monthly claims.</li>
    <li>To ensure accurate record-keeping of claims submitted by IC lecturers and approved by Academic Managers and HR personnel.</li>
    <li>To provide administrative reporting and auditing for the Programme Coordinators and HR departments.</li>
    <li>To notify you of any updates or actions needed for your claims.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing and Access</h2>
<p>We respect your privacy, and your data will only be shared with authorized personnel:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Lecturers:</strong> Can only access their own claims and supporting documentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Academic Managers:</strong> Have access to lecturer claims for review, approval, or rejection.</li>
    <li><strong>HR Personnel:</strong> Have access to approved claims and supporting documents for payroll processing.</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not share your personal data with any third-party organizations unless required by law or for legal proceedings.</p>

<h2>4. Data Security</h2>
<p>We take appropriate security measures to protect your personal information. These include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Encrypted transmission of data over secure channels (HTTPS).</li>
    <li>Access control measures, ensuring that only authorized users can access sensitive data.</li>
    <li>Regular security audits and updates to safeguard against vulnerabilities.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
<p>We retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy or as required by legal regulations. Typically, claim-related data is retained for a period defined by the institution's policies on financial and employment records.</p>

<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Access:</strong> You can request access to the personal data we hold about you.</li>
    <li><strong>Correction:</strong> You can request corrections or updates to your personal information if it is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
    <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request the deletion of your personal data where legally permissible.</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in legal, technical, or business developments. We will notify you of any significant changes through the system and update the date at the top of this page.</p>

<h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, please contact the system administrator or HR department.</p>
